{
  "text": "The VVG stain allowed visualization of internal elastic lamina degeneration, thrombosis, and cellular infiltration for each group [CITATION_1] (Fig. 2a, b) . Quantification of unruptured IA diameter (Rag1 508.11 ± 92.10 μm, WT 367.14 ± 65.36 μm) and IA wall thickness (Rag1 70.60 ± 6.09 μm, WT 54.35 ± 11.08 μm) was not significantly different between the groups (Fig. 2c, d ). Macrophage infiltration in the IA tissue was confirmed in all animals with the CD68 stain (Fig. 3a, b) . CD68 CTF quantification for the WT group (81.21 ± 16.33 AU, n = 5) showed no significant differences from the Rag1 group (64.85 ± 18.60 AU, n = 6, p = 0.34, Fig. 3c ).",
  "correct_citation": {
